description.narrative: By 2023, health facilities and communities are equipped to provide necessary immunization services, including logistics, commodities and skills, to children and pregnant women in 15 targeted regions., which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care (Covid), Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 1.12 - Appui sur le financment de la Sante et CSU

description.narrative: In 2021 routine immunization services were impacted by the COVID-19 epidemic and other emergencies. Lower coverage rates demonstrate this.UNICEF’s support was nevertheless key to make progress on different agendas: contracting of companies for the construction of the national EPI warehouse, continuing improvement of the cold chain with Ultra-Cold-Chain for the COVID vaccines, successful advocacy to Government to respect its financial commitment to routine vaccination, responses to Polio and COVID epidemics, improve immunization data quality. 10 out of 15 supported regions showed results above the national average. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/01/2022
